he  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Marget Pool was born in 1243, in Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom. She married William Clement about 1263, in Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1243–":"1243–Surnud","1244–1305":"1244–1305","1264–1294":"1264–1294","1243–Female":"1243–Surnud","Abt 1263":"umbes 1263","1305":"1305","8 January 1264":"8. jaanuar 1264","1244":"1244","1243":"1243","1264":"1264","1294":"1294","Genaur Gly, Cardigan, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Pennardd, Cardigan, Wales":"Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1243–":"1243–Kuollut","1244–1305":"1244–1305","1264–1294":"1264–1294","1243–Female":"1243–Kuollut","Abt 1263":"noin 1263","1305":"1305","8 January 1264":"8. tammikuuta 1264","1244":"1244","1243":"1243","1264":"1264","1294":"1294","Genaur Gly, Cardigan, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pennardd, Cardigan, Wales":"Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1243–":"1243–Décédée","1244–1305":"1244–1305","1264–1294":"1264–1294","1243–Female":"1243–Décédée","Abt 1263":"environ 1263","1305":"1305","8 January 1264":"8 janvier 1264","1244":"1244","1243":"1243","1264":"1264","1294":"1294","Genaur Gly, Cardigan, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Pennardd, Cardigan, Wales":"Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Marget Pool est née